  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cardiac output, the amount of blood pumped by the heart in one minute, will be measured in
      pediatric patients undergoing surgery involving cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB). Cardiac output
      will be measured after cardiopulmonary bypass using a device that employs ultrasound dilution
      technology. At times, cardiac output will be measured during a procedure called modified
      ultrafiltration (MUF). The ultrasound dilution cardiac output measurements will be validated
      or compared with cardiac output measurements made using other FDA approved techniques and
      devices.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
